sub_title: Cross-disciplinary beast, making disruptive technologies and innovation work for humans
summary:
I’m currently researching human-robot interaction, ethical AI, legal personhood of artificial agents and the frameworks in which they exist, specifically by innovative application of digital technology. I am drawn to de-puzzling life’s big questions with others by digging into their flesh with all the tools I have collected over the years in a spirit of collaboration, respect and interdisciplinarity. 

Throughout my professional career, I have been an implementor, coordinator and manager of numerous projects starting in international non-government D&G institutions and later CSR initiatives of global FMCG brands. My problem-solving nature got me into product development and analytical CRM, where based on the data-driven insight of my division, we designed technical solutions and  services for banking experience. In the two years at MediaTech MSc at Leiden, Netherlands, I polished my hardware and programming skills and developed a more sophisticated approach to research.

My multicultural interdisciplinary professional and academic journey developed me into a well-rounded, passionate, research driven and technically equipped problem solver, dedicated to responsibility by design and an optimistic view on the future of humanity.

Let’s address difficult questions together!

Contact me for any collaborations
